{
 "title": "Smack-In",
 "children": [
  {
   "title": "Overview",
   "lines": [
    "Standalone loop",
    "glitcher that reads",
    "Move's audio input",
    "directly (mic, line",
    "or USB-C audio).",
    "",
    "Use it in a sound",
    "generator slot; no",
    "upstream input",
    "module is needed.",
    "",
    "Grabs a quantized",
    "loop, slices it,",
    "and rolls seeded",
    "random FX plus a",
    "new slice order.",
    "",
    "The pattern repeats",
    "each pass until you",
    "re-roll it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Quick Start",
   "lines": [
    "1. Set Loop Len.",
    "2. Play something",
    " into Move's input.",
    "3. Hit Capture to",
    " grab the last",
    " loop length.",
    "4. A/B to punch",
    " between clean",
    " and pattern.",
    "5. Re-Roll for a",
    " new pattern.",
    "",
    "Or: Arm, then play.",
    "Recording starts on",
    "the next step and",
    "stops after the",
    "loop length."
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Knobs",
   "children": [
    {
     "title": "Chain UI Knobs",
     "lines": [
      "In the chain editor",
      "knobs 1-8 are:",
      "",
      "1: FX Density",
      "2: Order Density",
      "3: Loop Length",
      "4: Slice Res",
      "5: Wet",
      "6: Pitch Range",
      "7: AB Quantize",
      "8: Seed",
      "",
      "Hold Shift: knob",
      "page 2 (Pan L/R,",
      "Channels, Transport,",
      "BPM, Monitor); the",
      "steps show only the",
      "pinned slices.",
      "",
      "Wet = how effected",
      "the loop is: 0 =",
      "clean loop, 100 =",
      "full pattern. The",
      "loop always plays;",
      "dry input follows",
      "the Monitor pad."
     ]
    },
    {
     "title": "Knob Pages",
     "lines": [
      "On the param pages:",
      "",
      "Main knobs 1-8:",
      "Loop Len, Slice Res,",
      "FX Density, Order,",
      "Wet, Pitch Range,",
      "AB Quantize, Seed.",
      "",
      "Perform knobs 1-8:",
      "A/B, FX, Order, Wet,",
      "Pitch, AB Quantize,",
      "Pad Play, Pad Rate.",
      "Capture, Arm, Roll,",
      "Clear, Detect BPM:",
      "select in the list.",
      "",
      "Setup knobs 1-8:",
      "Wet, Pitch Range,",
      "AB Quantize, Seed,",
      "Transport, Channels,",
      "Pan L, Pan R."
     ]
    }
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Pads & Steps",
   "lines": [
    "Bottom-left pads:",
    "",
    "Capture: retro-grab",
    " (green)",
    "Arm: record next",
    " step (red)",
    "A/B: clean loop or",
    " pattern (white)",
    "Re-Roll: new",
    " pattern (blue)",
    "Clear: drop loop",
    " (orange, above",
    " Capture)",
    "",
    "Hardware Capture",
    "button: retro-grab.",
    "",
    "Steps 1-16 show the",
    "slice pattern, one",
    "color per effect,",
    "white is playhead.",
    "Press a step to",
    "mute its effect;",
    "press again to",
    "restore it.",
    "",
    "HOLD Re-Roll to",
    "clear every pinned",
    "slice and roll a",
    "fresh pattern.",
    "",
    "Loops over 16",
    "slices:",
    "5th bottom pad steps",
    "through 16-slice",
    "pages.",
    "",
    "HOLD A/B: momentary",
    "punch \u2014 flips while",
    "held, snaps back on",
    "release."
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Pad Play",
   "lines": [
    "In a slot editor",
    "Move's pads play",
    "notes into smack-in",
    "- with Pad Play On",
    "each note triggers",
    "a pattern cell:",
    "note % slices.",
    "",
    "Quantized: fires on",
    "the next Pad Rate",
    "boundary (default",
    "1/4 = the beat) and",
    "repeats there while",
    "held. Release goes",
    "back to the loop -",
    "the timeline keeps",
    "running under it.",
    "",
    "Velocity = volume.",
    "Newest held pad",
    "wins; release falls",
    "back to the older",
    "one.",
    "",
    "Pad Play + Rate:",
    "Setup page, or the",
    "web editor."
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Effects",
   "lines": [
    "22 slice effects:",
    "",
    "retrigger, reverse,",
    "pitch (varispeed),",
    "half/double speed,",
    "gate chop, buzz,",
    "bitcrush, repeat",
    "after split, reverse",
    "after split,",
    "tape stop and start,",
    "vinyl scratch,",
    "envelope shapes,",
    "pan tricks, filter",
    "sweeps, vowel",
    "filter, tonal delay,",
    "granular freeze,",
    "synced delay and",
    "ping-pong,",
    "distortion, phaser,",
    "gated reverb.",
    "",
    "FX Density sets how",
    "many slices get an",
    "effect; Order sets",
    "slice reshuffling."
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Dual Mono",
   "lines": [
    "Channels (Setup):",
    "Stereo or Dual Mono.",
    "",
    "Dual Mono treats L",
    "and R inputs as two",
    "mono signals, each",
    "with its own effect",
    "pattern, panned",
    "into the stereo",
    "field (Pan L/Pan R).",
    "",
    "Bottom pad row 7:",
    "toggle the mode.",
    "Pad 8: tap = edit L",
    "or R lane; hold +",
    "knob 1 or 2 = pans.",
    "",
    "A side plays the",
    "raw stereo loop;",
    "B side plays the",
    "panned lanes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Seed & Re-Roll",
   "lines": [
    "Seed browses",
    "patterns by number:",
    "the same seed always",
    "gives the same",
    "pattern.",
    "",
    "Re-Roll varies the",
    "current seed for a",
    "fresh pattern; dial",
    "the Seed knob to",
    "return to the",
    "canonical one."
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Feedback Guard",
   "lines": [
    "Speakers on with no",
    "line-in cable means",
    "the internal mic",
    "can feed back.",
    "",
    "When that risk is",
    "present the input",
    "monitoring is muted",
    "automatically: the",
    "Monitor pad turns",
    "red, capture still",
    "works, and the loop",
    "stays audible.",
    "",
    "Tap the Monitor pad",
    "to override, or",
    "plug in headphones",
    "or a line-in cable",
    "to restore it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "BPM Detect",
   "lines": [
    "Shift + Re-Roll",
    "listens to the last",
    "8 seconds of input",
    "and detects its",
    "tempo (60-180 BPM).",
    "",
    "The result becomes",
    "the free-run tempo,",
    "so Capture grabs",
    "true bars of the",
    "source. Shown as",
    "@BPM in the title.",
    "",
    "MIDI clock always",
    "wins when running.",
    "Needs material with",
    "clear hits; pads",
    "and drones report",
    "no tempo."
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Sync & Transport",
   "lines": [
    "Set Move's MIDI",
    "Clock to Out so",
    "Smack locks to the",
    "transport (same as",
    "the Arp).",
    "",
    "Without it, Smack",
    "free-runs at the",
    "project tempo.",
    "",
    "Transport (Setup):",
    "Follow: Move stop",
    "pauses the loop,",
    "play restarts it.",
    "Free: keep looping."
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Presets",
   "lines": [
    "Module presets save",
    "all knobs, the seed",
    "and re-roll state,",
    "plus slice mutes.",
    "",
    "Audio is not saved:",
    "capture a new loop",
    "after loading."
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Web Editor",
   "lines": [
    "Open the schwung",
    "manager in a browser",
    "(move.local) and go",
    "to Remote UI.",
    "",
    "oversmack: Tool tab.",
    "smack-in: its slot.",
    "",
    "Full slice grid,",
    "per-slice effect +",
    "parameter editing,",
    "effect presets, and",
    "named layouts that",
    "re-apply a whole",
    "pattern (seed +",
    "pins) to any loop.",
    "",
    "Edits sync live in",
    "both directions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Screen Reader",
   "lines": [
    "With the screen",
    "reader on (Global",
    "Settings), the chain",
    "editor announces",
    "pads, knob changes",
    "and loop state."
   ]
  }
 ]
}
